We use 1.59 rather than 1.62 as there are linking errors when building DLLs that depend on boost log.
A. Windows
1. replace the following in boost\config\user.hpp to disable auto library select
From
// #define BOOST_ALL_NO_LIB
To 
#ifndef BOOST_ALL_NO_LIB
#define BOOST_ALL_NO_LIB
#endif

#ifdef _MSC_VER
#ifndef BOOST_USE_WINAPI_VERSION
#define BOOST_USE_WINAPI_VERSION BOOST_WINAPI_VERSION_WIN7
#endif
#endif

Patch include/boost/iostreams/detail/config/fpos.hpp in iostream according to this:
https://github.com/boostorg/iostreams/pull/57

3. build and install boost as 64-bit static with dynamic runtime library
bootstrap.bat
b2 address-model=64 link=static runtime-link=shared -j 15 install
b2 address-model=64 link=shared runtime-link=shared --with-python -j 15 install

B. Linux
1. build
./bootstrap.sh --prefix=/home/rcheng/boost
./b2 cxxflags=-fPIC -j 15 address-model=64 install

C. Mavenize
3. use prepare.sh copy and rename necessary headers and libraries into individual lib folder

4. maven clean deploy
